snippet.textDisplay:
The version we now know for the Magpie numbers was created for the TV show Magpie (ITV's answer to Blue Peter) in the 70s. The original version was much darker so was changed to be more children-friendly. Originally it was...


One for sorrow,
Two for mirth
Three for a funeral,
Four for birth
Five for heaven
Six for hell
Seven for the devil, his own self


My mother was brought up on that one! Scary!
